    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="654"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/198</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Swiss Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SH1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sulzer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of April 24 in which you enumerate the terms under which the Imperial
                    German Government will grant safe conduct to vessels engaged in the
                    transportation of supplies to Switzerland.</p>
                <pb facs="0778" n="1612" xml:id="pg_1612"/>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to inform you that the terms for the granting of the
                    safe conduct are acceptable to this Government, provided the United States
                    Government receives through you definite assurances that all submarine
                    commanders have received the necessary instructions from the Imperial German
                    Government guaranteeing safe conduct to these vessels before such vessels sail
                    for Cette. An exception, however, must be made in respect to the former Dutch
                    vessels <hi rend="italic">Bellatrix, Alcor</hi>, and <hi rend="italic"
                        >Merak</hi> which, according to a decision already reached, will proceed
                    under proper convoy to an Atlantic port in France there to deliver their
                    cargoes.</p>
                <p>In spite of this decision, the Government of the United States will allow one of
                    these vessels to proceed to Cette under the terms of safe conduct described in
                    your note, provided the assurances mentioned above are received by this
                    Government before this vessel sails.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
